<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFE46839459A31F9BED2FABD" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE46839459A31F9BED2FABD" blockId="17.[151,1437,941,1328]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE46839459A31F9BB40FA81" bold="true" box="[199,315,1266,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previously 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE46839449E31F9B8EDFA81" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2010" box="[451,662,1266,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stuarti">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE46839449E31F9B8EDFA81" box="[451,662,1266,1292]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="300">Wellsomina stuarti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from three sites in each of the NT and Kimberley Region of WA (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE46839447B301DBB97FABD" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[294,492,1302,1328]" pageId="17" pageNumber="300" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref14689" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2010) Descriptions of 2 new genera and 13 new species of caddisflies from Australia (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 2415 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2415.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Cartwright, 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The species is recorded from a further eleven sites in the NT.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
